solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int rangeBitwiseAnd(int left, int right) {
        while (left < right) {
            right &= right - 1;
        }
        return right;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Repeatedly clears the lowest set bit of right until right ≤ left; the remaining bits are the common prefix of all numbers in the range, which is the bitwise AND of the entire interval.

